People here still talk about some stalker called Otter. They say he was one of the best, came to the Zone in the very first year. He was even on Strelok's team.
And then one day he got too close to the Brain Scorcher and that's it. People saw him collapse, and then a few minutes later he suddenly got up and staggered further into the Scorcher. Never seen from again.

<string id="dm_information_69">
	<text>I'm stuck here, alright? Stuck. I want to go home and they're not letting me. That's all the news. The guys that walk deep into the Zone, the ones that have been around, they say different things. And at times they bring goodies too, enough to make you jealous. They say there are places like mounds of gold: artefacts all for the taking. Granted not many will get there, and even less will make it back with the loot.</text>
</string>

<string id="dm_information_70">
	<text>Did you hear the rumour that the Zone is growing? I think it's true: I saw this frightening humanoid mutant right by the perimeter. Previously you could only run into these freakish things in the centre of the Zone. Things aren't looking good.
</text>
</string>

So many squaddies come to the Dead City and need additional training. They're combat ready, but they're not 'Zone ready'. They're not used to wearing gas masks day and night, or checking for anomalies on patrol. We've designated some guys as trainers and had their contracts amended. All they do is teach the new Mercs about the Zone before passing them onto another squad for the proper jobs. Hopefully we won't lose more guys to stupid mistakes.

You heard about the 'teachers'? Some guys just get paid to lead newbies around the southern parts of the Zone, telling them to throw bolts, and showing them all the anomalies and wildlife. They need to get people acclimidaised to the Zone instead of walking into Whirligigs or dying of radiation poisoning. It sounds like a pretty easy job. Well paid too.
